						p At age 13 I turned down an art scholarship and took up programming in Visual Basic. By age 16 I had moved on to Perl and C++, had taken over my school computer network (for err&hellip; research&hellip;), and had also started my own web design company, just as the web was taking off. I studied Computer Science and Graphic Design at university so have both a technical and creative background.
						p Today my preferred technology stack is Jade, Stylus, and CoffeeScript, with Gulp running tasks, NPM for package management, Browserify for tying in dependencies, Yeoman for scaffolding, Jasmine and PhantomJS for testing, and Git for version control and continuous deployment. My JavaScript framework of choice is AngularJS (used on this site) in the front and ExpressJS at the back. I work primarily on an iMac and a Macbook Pro, using Sublime Text 3 and the terminal. I design vector images using Adobe Illustrator and websites and web apps using the Chrome web browser, which has superb tools for debugging and measuring performance. You'll find more information about  
							a(href="#skills", title="Find out more about what I can do") my skills and services here
							| .
